                "id": 21,
                "title": "Mind if I ask you a question?",
                "blog": "<p>\n</br>\n</p>\n<p>\n    I've had the privilege of working for businesses large and small. An array of different customers and focus from\n    Video Games to Home Loans to Health Insurance to... you name it! Regardless of the place, I've wanted to\n    learn outside my lane. It's not easy in corporations.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n    The companies have tried to set it up, it just doesn't work well in my experience. Want to learn more about our\n        legal strategy? We will do a <i>lunch and learn</i>. Have questions about how to manage your budget? Attend this online\n    course! Want to talk directly with our Chief Financial Officer? Not on your life.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n        Being an entrepreneur I have found the opposite to be true. Resources in other disciplines, experts in fields I\n        need to learn but do not know are more than willing to help a boy out with his dream. The list over the years\n        is long and there are many thank you messages deserved.\n    </p>\n    <p>\n    <strong>Today was another of those days</strong>\n        </br>\n        </br>\n        I am not an accountant. I run into the same trap most software developer founders find. I like to code, and\nwhen things get sticky, that is what I do. Not sure which top business rule it is exactly, but I am pretty sure making money is\n        top 10? At least top 20? Being able to speak to financials beyond back of the napkin? Yeah... I know at some\n        point I am going to need that.\n</br>\n    </p>\n    <p>\n    Through a mutual Podcast 'Like', I found Tony Wilson of Accquip. He posted and podcasted (is that a word? why is\n        spellcheck not happy with podcasted?? He is a podcaster is what I'm trying to say!) about software developers\n        like me doing impossible things like we do; starting our own companies. I had questions, and he agreed to talk\n        them through with me. Turns out, he knows how to help financially plan to make that impossible... possible!\n        I still have the mindset that access to resources like this is hard. Tony made it super easy, has great\n        ideas for software founders, and I cannot thank him enough for the help.\n    </p>\n</br>\n<p>You can find his <a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A6QCAwW1lXg'>youtube channel</a> here. Tony, thank you\n    again!</p>\n</br>\n</p>\n<a href='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A6QCAwW1lXg'>\n<img\n        id=left-image\n        src='https://wildalmonds.com/api/uploads/11f4fdde-df1e-4e13-9fd3-56890e6eda38_tonyWilson.png'\n        alt='Tony Wilson'\n/>\n</a>\n<p>",
